## Analysis: @chkit/plugin-backfill (v0.1.0-beta.15)

### Overview

The `@chkit/plugin-backfill` package is a chkit plugin that provides time-windowed data backfill operations with checkpointing. It splits a time range into deterministic chunks, persists an immutable plan to disk, then executes each chunk sequentially with retry logic and event logging. The plugin does NOT actually execute SQL against ClickHouse -- it simulates chunk execution (the `executeChunk` function only tracks state transitions, not real database calls). It registers six CLI subcommands (`plan`, `run`, `resume`, `status`, `cancel`, `doctor`) and two lifecycle hooks (`onConfigLoaded`, `onCheck`/`onCheckReport`).

All source files reside under:
